04/01/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The economy and finance ministry issued a statement Monday (3 January), saying it plans to tighten control over public spending.
One measure envisions cutting all credit lines to EU-funded projects that have failed to show progress thus far.
In other news Monday, Otto Rehhagel, the German coach who led Greece to a stunning victory in the 2004 European football championships, was named "Person of the Year" by the readers of the popular Ta Nea daily newspaper.
Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis came in second.
(ANA - 04/01/05;
MPA, AP - 03/01/05)
